 24 var Native = function(options){
 25 	options = options || {};
 26 
 27 	var afterImplement = options.afterImplement || function(){};
 28 	var generics = options.generics;
 29 	generics = (generics !== false);
 30 	var legacy = options.legacy;
 31 	var initialize = options.initialize;
 32 	var protect = options.protect;
 33 	var name = options.name;
 34 
 35 	var object = initialize || legacy;
 36 
 37 	object.constructor = Native;
 38 	object.$family = {name: 'native'};
 39 	if (legacy && initialize) object.prototype = legacy.prototype;
 40 	object.prototype.constructor = object;
 41 
 42 	if (name){
 43 		var family = name.toLowerCase();
 44 		object.prototype.$family = {name: family};
 45 		Native.typize(object, family);
 46 	}
 47 
 48 	var add = function(obj, name, method, force){
 49 		if (!protect || force || !obj.prototype[name]) obj.prototype[name] = method;
 50 		if (generics) Native.genericize(obj, name, protect);
 51 		afterImplement.call(obj, name, method);
 52 		return obj;
 53 	};
 54 	
 55 	object.implement = function(a1, a2, a3){
 56 		if (typeof a1 == 'string') return add(this, a1, a2, a3);
 57 		for (var p in a1) add(this, p, a1[p], a2);
 58 		return this;
 59 	};
 60 	
 61 	object.alias = function(a1, a2, a3){
 62 		if (typeof a1 == 'string'){
 63 			a1 = this.prototype[a1];
 64 			if (a1) add(this, a2, a1, a3);
 65 		} else {
 66 			for (var a in a1) this.alias(a, a1[a], a2);
 67 		}
 68 		return this;
 69 	};
 70 
 71 	return object;
 72 };

 78 Native.genericize = function(object, property, check){
 79 	if ((!check || !object[property]) && typeof object.prototype[property] == 'function') object[property] = function(){
 80 		var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments);
 81 		return object.prototype[property].apply(args.shift(), args);
 82 	};
 83 };

143 function $unlink(object){
144 	var unlinked;
145 	
146 	switch ($type(object)){
147 		case 'object':
148 			unlinked = {};
149 			for (var p in object) unlinked[p] = $unlink(object[p]);
150 		break;
151 		case 'hash':
152 			unlinked = $unlink(object.getClean());
153 		break;
154 		case 'array':
155 			unlinked = [];
156 			for (var i = 0, l = object.length; i < l; i++) unlinked[i] = $unlink(object[i]);
157 		break;
158 		default: return object;
159 	}
160 	
161 	return unlinked;
162 };

164 function $merge(){
165 	var mix = {};
166 	for (var i = 0, l = arguments.length; i < l; i++){
167 		var object = arguments[i];
168 		if ($type(object) != 'object') continue;
169 		for (var key in object){
170 			var op = object[key], mp = mix[key];
171 			mix[key] = (mp && $type(op) == 'object' && $type(mp) == 'object') ? $merge(mp, op) : $unlink(op);
172 		}
173 	}
174 	return mix;
175 };

206 function $type(obj){
207 	if (obj == undefined) return false;
208 	if (obj.$family) return (obj.$family.name == 'number' && !isFinite(obj)) ? false : obj.$family.name;
209 	if (obj.nodeName){
210 		switch (obj.nodeType){
211 			case 1: return 'element';
212 			case 3: return (/\S/).test(obj.nodeValue) ? 'textnode' : 'whitespace';
213 		}
214 	} else if (typeof obj.length == 'number'){
215 		if (obj.callee) return 'arguments';
216 		else if (obj.item) return 'collection';
217 	}
218 	return typeof obj;
219 };

275 function $A(iterable){

277 		var array = [];
278 		for (var i = 0, l = iterable.length; i < l; i++) array[i] = iterable[i];

280 	}

334 function $exec(text){
335 	if (!text) return text;
336 	if (window.execScript){
337 		window.execScript(text);
338 	} else {
339 		var script = document.createElement('script');
340 		script.setAttribute('type', 'text/javascript');
341 		script.text = text;
342 		document.head.appendChild(script);
343 		document.head.removeChild(script);
344 	}
345 	return text;
346 };

558 Function.implement({
559 
560 	extend: function(properties){
561 		for (var property in properties) this[property] = properties[property];
562 		return this;

564 
565 	create: function(options){
566 		var self = this;
567 		options = options || {};
568 		return function(event){
569 			var args = options.arguments;
570 			args = (args != undefined) ? $splat(args) : Array.slice(arguments, (options.event) ? 1 : 0);
571 			if (options.event) args = [event || window.event].extend(args);
572 			var returns = function(){
573 				return self.apply(options.bind || null, args);
574 			};
575 			if (options.delay) return setTimeout(returns, options.delay);
576 			if (options.periodical) return setInterval(returns, options.periodical);
577 			if (options.attempt) return $try(returns);
578 			return returns();
579 		};
580 	},
581

583 		return this.create({arguments: args, bind: bind});
584 	},
585 
586 	attempt: function(args, bind){
587 		return this.create({arguments: args, bind: bind, attempt: true})();
588 	},
589 
590 	bind: function(bind, args){
591 		return this.create({bind: bind, arguments: args});
592 	},

595 		return this.create({bind: bind, event: true, arguments: args});
596 	},
597

600 	},
601 
602 	periodical: function(interval, bind, args){
603 		return this.create({periodical: interval, bind: bind, arguments: args})();

1021 			return self;

1041 Class.Mutators = {
1042   
1043   Implements: function(self, klasses){
1044   	$splat(klasses).each(function(klass){
1045   		$extend(self, ($type(klass) == 'class') ? new klass($empty) : klass);
1046   	});
1047   },
1048   
1049   Extends: function(self, klass){
1050   	var instance = new klass($empty);
1051   	delete instance.parent;
1052   	delete instance.parentOf;
1053 
1054   	for (var key in instance){
1055   		var current = self[key], previous = instance[key];
1056   		if (current == undefined){
1057   			self[key] = previous;
1058   			continue;
1059   		}
1060 
1061   		var ctype = $type(current), ptype = $type(previous);
1062   		if (ctype != ptype) continue;
1063 
1064   		switch (ctype){
1065   			case 'function': 
1066   				// this code will be only executed if the current browser does not support function.caller (currently only opera).
1067   				// we replace the function code with brute force. Not pretty, but it will only be executed if function.caller is not supported.
1068 
1069   				if (!arguments.callee.caller) self[key] = eval('(' + String(current).replace(/\bthis\.parent\(\s*(\))?/g, function(full, close){
1070   					return 'arguments.callee._parent_.call(this' + (close || ', ');
1071   				}) + ')');
1072 
1073   				// end "opera" code
1074   				self[key]._parent_ = previous;
1075   			  break;
1076   			case 'object': self[key] = $merge(previous, current);
1077   		}
1078 
1079   	}
1080 
1081   	self.parent = function(){
1082   		return arguments.callee.caller._parent_.apply(this, arguments);
1083   	};
1084 
1085   	self.parentOf = function(descendant){
1086   		return descendant._parent_.apply(this, Array.slice(arguments, 1));
1087   	};
1088   }

2382 		if (Selectors.Cache.nth[argument]) return Selectors.Cache.nth[argument];

5179 		this.coord = this.getCoords.bind(this);
5180 	},
5181 
5182 	start: function(){
5183 		this.listener.addEvent('mousemove', this.coord);
5184 	},
5185 
5186 	stop: function(){
5187 		this.listener.removeEvent('mousemove', this.coord);
5188 		this.timer = $clear(this.timer);
5189 	},
5190 
5191 	getCoords: function(event){
5192 		this.page = (this.listener.get('tag') == 'body') ? event.client : event.page;
5193 		if (!this.timer) this.timer = this.scroll.periodical(50, this);
5194 	},
5195 
5196 	scroll: function(){
5197 		var size = this.element.getSize(), scroll = this.element.getScroll(), pos = this.element.getPosition(), change = {'x': 0, 'y': 0};
5198 		for (var z in this.page){
5199 			if (this.page[z] < (this.options.area + pos[z]) && scroll[z] != 0)
5200 				change[z] = (this.page[z] - this.options.area - pos[z]) * this.options.velocity;
5201 			else if (this.page[z] + this.options.area > (size[z] + pos[z]) && size[z] + size[z] != scroll[z])
5202 				change[z] = (this.page[z] - size[z] + this.options.area - pos[z]) * this.options.velocity;
5203 		}
5204 		if (change.y || change.x) this.fireEvent('change', [scroll.x + change.x, scroll.y + change.y]);
5205 	}
5206

5217 var Accordion = new Class({

5225 		show: false,
5226 		height: true,
5227 		width: false,

5229 		fixedHeight: false,
5230 		fixedWidth: false,
5231 		wait: false,
5232 		alwaysHide: false
5233 	},
5234 
5235 	initialize: function(){
5236 		var params = Array.link(arguments, {'container': Element.type, 'options': Object.type, 'togglers': $defined, 'elements': $defined});
5237 		this.parent(params.elements, params.options);
5238 		this.togglers = $$(params.togglers);
5239 		this.container = $(params.container);
5240 		this.previous = -1;
5241 		if (this.options.alwaysHide) this.options.wait = true;
5242 		if ($chk(this.options.show)){
5243 			this.options.display = false;
5244 			this.previous = this.options.show;
5245 		}
5246 		if (this.options.start){
5247 			this.options.display = false;
5248 			this.options.show = false;
5249 		}
5250 		this.effects = {};
5251 		if (this.options.opacity) this.effects.opacity = 'fullOpacity';
5252 		if (this.options.width) this.effects.width = this.options.fixedWidth ? 'fullWidth' : 'offsetWidth';
5253 		if (this.options.height) this.effects.height = this.options.fixedHeight ? 'fullHeight' : 'scrollHeight';
5254 		for (var i = 0, l = this.togglers.length; i < l; i++) this.addSection(this.togglers[i], this.elements[i]);
5255 		this.elements.each(function(el, i){
5256 			if (this.options.show === i){
5257 				this.fireEvent('active', [this.togglers[i], el]);
5258 			} else {
5259 				for (var fx in this.effects) el.setStyle(fx, 0);
5260 			}
5261 		}, this);
5262 		if ($chk(this.options.display)) this.display(this.options.display);
5263 	},
5264 
5265 	addSection: function(toggler, element, pos){
5266 		toggler = $(toggler);
5267 		element = $(element);
5268 		var test = this.togglers.contains(toggler);
5269 		var len = this.togglers.length;
5270 		this.togglers.include(toggler);
5271 		this.elements.include(element);
5272 		if (len && (!test || pos)){
5273 			pos = $pick(pos, len - 1);
5274 			toggler.inject(this.togglers[pos], 'before');
5275 			element.inject(toggler, 'after');
5276 		} else if (this.container && !test){
5277 			toggler.inject(this.container);
5278 			element.inject(this.container);
5279 		}
5280 		var idx = this.togglers.indexOf(toggler);
5281 		toggler.addEvent('click', this.display.bind(this, idx));
5282 		if (this.options.height) element.setStyles({'padding-top': 0, 'border-top': 'none', 'padding-bottom': 0, 'border-bottom': 'none'});
5283 		if (this.options.width) element.setStyles({'padding-left': 0, 'border-left': 'none', 'padding-right': 0, 'border-right': 'none'});
5284 		element.fullOpacity = 1;
5285 		if (this.options.fixedWidth) element.fullWidth = this.options.fixedWidth;
5286 		if (this.options.fixedHeight) element.fullHeight = this.options.fixedHeight;
5287 		element.setStyle('overflow', 'hidden');
5288 		if (!test){
5289 			for (var fx in this.effects) element.setStyle(fx, 0);
5290 		}
5291 		return this;
5292 	},
5293 
5294 	display: function(index){
5295 		index = ($type(index) == 'element') ? this.elements.indexOf(index) : index;
5296 		if ((this.timer && this.options.wait) || (index === this.previous && !this.options.alwaysHide)) return this;
5297 		this.previous = index;
5298 		var obj = {};
5299 		this.elements.each(function(el, i){
5300 			obj[i] = {};
5301 			var hide = (i != index) || (this.options.alwaysHide && (el.offsetHeight > 0));
5302 			this.fireEvent(hide ? 'background' : 'active', [this.togglers[i], el]);
5303 			for (var fx in this.effects) obj[i][fx] = hide ? 0 : el[this.effects[fx]];
5304 		}, this);
5305 		return this.start(obj);
5306 	}

5308 });
